            "notes": [
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Charm",
                  "pageId": 1016293,
                  "revisionId": 2719438,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Each instance of a buff has their own timer and are stackable; they do not overwrite each other. However, the HUD only shows the timer for the latest instance of a buff."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Charm",
                  "pageId": 1016293,
                  "revisionId": 2719438,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Every 27s there is a 40% chance to receive a random buff out of 6 buffs, getting a Triple Affinity Buff out of the 6 buff pool is 0.4*0.1 = 4% , getting the buff twice in a row is (4%) 2 = 0.16% , the duration of each buff is 120s which means at most there can only be 5 possible instances active at the same time. The chance of that is happening is (4%) 5 = 1.024×10 −5 % ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Charm",
                  "pageId": 1016293,
                  "revisionId": 2719438,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Buffs durations can be extended using Tek Enhance ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Charm",
                  "pageId": 1016293,
                  "revisionId": 2719438,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "With Tek Enhance each duration can increase to 156s, meaning 6 instances are possible. The chance of this happening is (4%) 6 = 4.1×10 −7 % ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Charm",
                  "pageId": 1016293,
                  "revisionId": 2719438,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Keeping in mind that all Affinity buffs are multiplicative, stacking an Affinity Booster(x2), an Affinity Blessing(+25% base Affinity gain), during an Affinity Weekend Booster(x2) adds up to 500% Affinity gain. Adding in the triple Affinity buff from Charm, it will stack respectively to 1,500% Affinity on one buff, 4,500% on two, 13,500% on three, 40,500% on four, 121,500% on five, and an immense 364,500% on 6 consecutive buffs. For reference, a Heavy Gunner worth 5,000 Affinity regularly would award an astounding 18,225,000 Affinity on kill."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Charm",
                  "pageId": 1016293,
                  "revisionId": 2719438,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "The Reinforced Shields buff can trigger on Warframes without Shields , but will not grant Overshields to them. It can also trigger when at maximum Overshields on other Warframes."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Charm",
                  "pageId": 1016293,
                  "revisionId": 2719438,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "The Energy refund buff can trigger on Warframes without Energy ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Charm",
                  "pageId": 1016293,
                  "revisionId": 2719438,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "The Critical Chance Bonus sets minimum Critical Chance on weapons to 200% . Weapons that already possess critical chance above this value remain unaffected."
                }
              },
